duck: throwback definition: reversion to an earlier type or phase.
Throwback style, a culturally outdated fashion from the overall postmodern past which has since become the norm once again
Throwback uniform, a sports uniform which mimics an older uniform of the team
Evolutionary throwback, a reversion to ancestral type
The Throwback, a 1978 satirical novel written by Tom Sharpe
Chicago Throwbacks, a team of the Premier Basketball League
